To install NMCLI utility:

#sudo yum install NetworkManager-tui

To up connection:

#nmcli connection up eth0

 nmcli networking on

To set static ip and gw to connection:

# nmcli con add type ethernet con-name static2 ifname enp0s3 ip4 192.168.1.50/24 gw4 192.168.1.1

From <https://www.tecmint.com/configure-network-connections-using-nmcli-tool-in-linux/> 

From <http://www.vassox.com/linux-general/install-nmtui-network-manager-on-centos-rhel/> 


GATEWAYDEV=network_interface
GATEWAY=default_gateway_ip


Linux add a default gateway (route) using ipcommand

#ip route add 192.168.1.0/24 dev eth0

From <https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/linux-route-add/> 

Add a permanent static route

#nano /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/route-eth0

172.16.5.0/24 via 10.0.0.101 dev eth0

From <https://my.esecuredata.com/index.php?/knowledgebase/article/2/add-a-static-route-on-centos>